      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-10-14T01:16:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m a bit concerned that we\u0027re losing the ordering property of the original IniFile implementation (which used a simple vector of (key,value) pairs). This is not a big deal, but when inspecting the content of .ini files generated by the emulator (e.g. harware-qemu.ini), this will randomize the order of the output. Could we at least sort the output by key name before writing it to a file?",
      "revId": "3c2c56b6a225ba0ac507b7fb8f978a51786535f9",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
